{% extends "layouts/standard_content.jinja" %}
{% from "components/heading.jinja" import heading %}
{% from "components/card.jinja" import card %}
{% from "components/contents.jinja" import contents %}
{% from "components/link.jinja" import link %}
{% from "components/list.jinja" import list, list_item %}
{% block mobile_article_title %}
  {% call heading() %}
    What we provide
  {% endcall %}
  <p>
    Find Case Law focuses on providing judgments and decisions from courts and tribunals in England and Wales. Understanding what we include – and what we don't – helps you know what to expect when searching.
  </p>
{% endblock mobile_article_title %}
{% block desktop_article_title %}
  {% call heading() %}
    What we provide
  {% endcall %}
  <p>
    Find Case Law focuses on providing judgments and decisions from courts and tribunals in England and Wales. Understanding what we include – and what we don't – helps you know what to expect when searching.
  </p>
{% endblock desktop_article_title %}
{% block article_navigation %}
  {% call contents(title="On this page") %}
    {% call list() %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        {% call link(href="#service-scope") %}
          Service scope
        {% endcall %}
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        {% call link(href="#coverage-details") %}
          Coverage details
        {% endcall %}
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        {% call link(href="#understanding-what-youll-find") %}
          Understanding what you'll find
        {% endcall %}
      {% endcall %}
    {% endcall %}
  {% endcall %}
{% endblock article_navigation %}
{% block article_content %}
  {% call heading(tag="h2") %}
    Service scope
  {% endcall %}
  <p>
    Find Case Law is designed to support open justice by making court judgments publicly
    accessible. We work with the judiciary to publish case law for legal research, public understanding, and accountability.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>What's included</strong>
  </p>
  {% call list(variant="bullets") %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      judgments from appellate courts (Supreme Court, Court of Appeal, High Court)
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      decisions from First–tier and Upper Tribunals
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      selected Crown Court and County Court cases
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      press Summaries for Supreme Court decisions
    {% endcall %}
  {% endcall %}
  <p>
    <strong>What's not included</strong>
  </p>
  <p>Find Case Law is a very comprehensive library but we don't include:</p>
  {% call list(variant="bullets") %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      most magistrates' court decisions
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      judgments that are subject to reporting restrictions
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      routine orders
    {% endcall %}
  {% endcall %}
  {% call heading(tag="h2") %}
    Coverage details
  {% endcall %}
  <p>
    {%- call link(href=url("home")) -%}
      About Find Case Law
    {%- endcall %}
    provides a detailed explanation of our service scope, what types of
    judgments we publish and what to include.
  </p>
  <p>The scope of Find Case Law continues to expand as we add more courts and enhance coverage of existing courts.</p>
  {% call heading(tag="h2") %}
    Understanding what you'll find
  {% endcall %}
  <p>
    Different courts and tribunals have different levels of coverage. Some have nearly complete
    recent records, while others are more selective. See our
    {%- call link(href=url("courts_and_date_coverage")) -%}
      Courts and date coverage
    {%- endcall %}
    for exactly what's available for each jurisdiction.
  </p>
  <p>
    Knowing our scope helps you search effectively and understand whether the case you're
    looking for should be in Find Case Law.
  </p>
{% endblock article_content %}
